cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.SI 

The paper focuses on the design of interactive intelligent systems, which involves the intersection of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use case presented in the paper involves information extraction (cs.IR) and the challenge of finding the right level of algorithmic support, which is relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) concerns. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for systematic investigation of the design space, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
